<subSubSection id="51ACDFA0182F9E45CF10FF5DA9DF255C" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="38F530020A512B4C7C34742B9FD2CB52" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E09201FA164F19DE8138546509C3ABB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Compared to the male genitalia of the holotype (fig. 17 in 
<bibRefCitation id="7770D2FBD9A45FE7EF2BC63D48644482" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" author="Wilkinson, C" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="407 - 517" refId="B26" refString="Wilkinson, C, 1968. A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 31 (4): 407 - 517, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" title="A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" volume="31" year="1968">Wilkinson 1968</bibRefCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="BBAEC8FE64F4B402C4EFDC318114E9B7" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. spilota" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="spilota">
<emphasis id="8ED5D0F16E24BBA02B1877A152EC57CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. spilota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the socii of the paratype examined are much broader and blunter, while the aedeagus and 8th segment have no distinct differences. Further study is needed to investigate whether this is intraspecific variation, or more than one species is present in the large type series.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
